==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pectoriloquy
<hw>Pec`to*ril"o*quy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>pectus</ets>, <ets>-oris</ets>, the breast + <ets>loqui</ets> to
speak: cf. F. <ets>pectoriloquie</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld>
<def>The distinct articulation of the sounds of a patient's voice, heard
on applying the ear to the chest in auscultation. It usually indicates
some morbid change in the lungs or pleural cavity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pectose</ent>⟦br⟧
